      "content": "The strongest philosophical argument against government regulation of the internet is the idea that any attempt to restrict online speech is a form of prior restraint, which is a fundamental threat to the First Amendment's protection of free speech. The Supreme Court has consistently ruled that prior restraint is unconstitutional, and government regulation of the internet can be seen as a form of prior restraint. This is because regulation can be used to censor or limit speech before it's even published, rather than punishing speech after it's occurred.",
